}}\n'''Neville Gallimore''' is a [[Canadian]] [[American football]] [[defensive tackle]] for the [[Dallas Cowboys]] of the [[National Football League]] (NFL). He played [[college football]] at [[Oklahoma Sooners football|Oklahoma]].\n\n==Early years==\nGallimore's parents were born and raised in Jamaica.  Gallimore attended the [[Canada Prep Academy]] in [[Welland]], [[Ontario]], Canada.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://ottawacitizen.com/sports/local-sports/living-the-dream-ottawas-neville-gallimore-has-his-sights-set-on-the-ncaa|title=Living the dream: Ottawa\u2019s Neville Gallimore has his sights set on the NCAA &#124; Ottawa Citizen|date=November 22, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/sports/football/neville-gallimore-of-ottawa-brings-a-small-football-first-school-major-notice/article21154967/|title=Neville Gallimore of Ottawa brings a small, football-first school major notice|via=The Globe and Mail}}</ref> He played in the 2015 [[U.S. Army All-American Bowl]], becoming the first Canadian to do so.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.mysanantonio.com/sports/high_school/high_school_football/article/Canadian-s-star-rising-in-the-U-S-5986270.php|title=Canadian\u2019s star rising in the U.S.|first=Ben|last=Baby|date=December 30, 2014|website=San Antonio Express-News}}</ref> After receiving 30 scholarship offers from U.S. colleges, Gallimore committed to the [[University of Oklahoma]] to play college football.<ref>[https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/ottawa/neville-gallimore-of-ottawa-excited-relieved-to-join-oklahoma-sooners-1.2890136 Neville Gallimore of Ottawa excited, relieved to join Oklahoma Sooners]</ref>\n\n==College career==\nGallimore redshirted his first year at Oklahoma in 2015. In 2016, he played in all 13 games and made six starts, recording 40 tackles and one sack.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://oklahoman.com/article/5525715/ou-football-from-ontario-to-norman-neville-gallimore-growing-as-a-sooner/|title=OU football: From Ontario to Norman, Nev